external.description: How do we meaningfully design assessment of and for learning when the presence of AI tools fundamentally changes the game? Earlier this term, I was invited to present to a group of school curriculum leaders who are preparing to reimagine assessment for the 2026 school year. The timing is both exciting and daunting. These leaders find themselves on the frontlines of a rapidly shifting educational landscape, grappling with the complex interplay of generative AI, cognitive development, academic integrity, digital equity, and evolving pedagogies.
external.title: From Levels to Learning: Rethinking AI Assessment in History Departments
